Modifications have been made to the original Bifrost source as part of building
Loopback Gateway (Apache License 2.0, Section 4(b)). Notable changes:

  - Added a Go workspace (go.work) so local sub-modules build against the
    in-tree core rather than a published release.
  - Added plugins/loopbackguard/: a guardrail engine plugin (15 request/text
    guardrails, an in-process regex PII/secret redactor, a Microsoft Presidio
    sidecar connector, and fail-closed PII blocking).
  - Added plugins/loopbackkafka/: a Kafka data connector publishing completed
    request/response telemetry (batching, backpressure, SASL/PLAIN).
  - Added plugins/prompts/: stored prompt-template resolution via request
    headers, with weighted version deployments.
  - Added plugins/modelcatalogresolver/: unprefixed-model -> provider lookup
    as a final pre-request fallback.
  - Added compliance and identity subsystems across core, framework, and the
    HTTP transport, including their configuration-store database migrations:
    RBAC (roles/permissions/assignments with enforcing middleware and a
    secure-setup flow), HMAC-signed audit logging with export and retention,
    SSO/SCIM (Keycloak, Okta, Microsoft Entra OIDC providers; inbound SCIM 2.0
    endpoint; attribute-to-role mapping), JWT authentication mapped to virtual
    keys, alert channels (Slack/PagerDuty/webhook dispatcher), guardrail and
    PII-rule configuration APIs, a per-provider circuit breaker, users and
    business units, MCP tool groups, and scoped admin API keys.
  - Rebranded the web UI from "Bifrost" to "Loopback Gateway" (~67 files) and
    added new workspace pages: guardrails, pii-redactor, circuit-breaker, rbac,
    scim, audit-logs, alert-channels, jwt-auth, prompt-repo, mcp-tool-groups,
    and observability.
  - Quarantined non-compiling draft files under docs/draft-stubs/ and added
    project documentation (ADRs, status/delivery records, roadmap).

